{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/376/comments/56820722.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/376#comment-56820722"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/376.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 376, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Is it possible to mount/load local folders into osrf/subt-virtual-testbed  image?"}, "content": {"raw": "To run bash instead of whatever is set to run in the image, you need to supply `--entrypoint` argument to `docker run` call. I have `run.bash`  where I don\u2019t reset `DOCKER_OPTS` which allows me to set them from the outside like this:\n\n`DOCKER_OPTS=\"--entrypoint /bin/bash\" ./run.bash osrf/subt-virtual-testbed:cloudsim_sim_latest` \n\nwhich gets me a terminal from any image.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>To run bash instead of whatever is set to run in the image, you need to supply <code>--entrypoint</code> argument to <code>docker run</code> call. I have <code>run.bash</code>  where I don\u2019t reset <code>DOCKER_OPTS</code> which allows me to set them from the outside like this:</p>\n<p><code>DOCKER_OPTS=\"--entrypoint /bin/bash\" ./run.bash osrf/subt-virtual-testbed:cloudsim_sim_latest</code> </p>\n<p>which gets me a terminal from any image.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-04-07T05:49:14.722814+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Zbyn\u011bk Winkler", "uuid": "{d253a02a-aa23-4c28-9bf2-75863acb0ee0}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd253a02a-aa23-4c28-9bf2-75863acb0ee0%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd253a02a-aa23-4c28-9bf2-75863acb0ee0%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/326a12c819c60ee18418b5d01000d03fd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsZW-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Zbyn\u011bk Winkler (robotika)", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:a92b5a4f-5b91-4853-8dec-b918bd975e70"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 56820722}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/376/comments/56847438.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt/issues/376#comment-56847438"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt/issues/376.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 376, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/subt.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/subt"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}ts=2272898"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "subt", "full_name": "osrf/subt", "uuid": "{3c95f6ad-c304-407c-b838-09597d836552}"}, "title": "Is it possible to mount/load local folders into osrf/subt-virtual-testbed  image?"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks! That seems to work for running it but haven\u2019t figure out how to pass the folder as input and have it load inside the image. Any suggestions? I really appreciate your help. \n\n\u200c", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks! That seems to work for running it but haven\u2019t figure out how to pass the folder as input and have it load inside the image. Any suggestions? I really appreciate your help. </p>\n<p>\u200c</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2020-04-07T21:28:56.111968+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Hector Escobar", "uuid": "{1c140a49-f2c5-4727-abd9-eb427bfe4253}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B1c140a49-f2c5-4727-abd9-eb427bfe4253%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B1c140a49-f2c5-4727-abd9-eb427bfe4253%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/8da90eb0e9b47c9adfc2893e5190483fd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.